features: Designed with a rigid LATCH system that locks the booster seat into place using your vehicles latch system providing additional stability in a collision. Made in North America.
Advanced safety features, including a high-impact copolymer frame, an energy-absorbing EPP foam reinforced headrest and a steel base sub-structure with integrated rigid-LATCH connectors.
Reclines: comfort is a must when it comes to long journeys. Oobr is designed with a recline system that offers up to 12 degrees of recline for sleeping comfort (latch Installation required).
Removable back for longer use: the back of the Oobr booster seat is removable for longer use with your growing child.
C-Zero Plus Performance fabrics are GREENGUARD Gold Certified and provide resistance to water-based stains using an innovative fluorine-free formula that’s free of halogenated flame retardants.
body.description: Built like the seat in your car, but sized for your child. Oobr is a high back booster seat that’s both Oobr safe and Oobr cool. Engineered to protect, it revolutionizes booster seating with advanced safety features, including a high-impact copolymer frame, an energy-absorbing EPP foam reinforced headrest and a steel base sub-structure with integrated rigid-LATCH connectors for enhanced seat stability. Rated a ‘Best Bet’ by the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety 10+ years in a row, Oobr offers the comfort and flexibility to grow, with a fully removable reclining seat back. Plus, its narrow design makes it easy to ride 3-across.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Clek Oobr Full Back Booster Seat Usage Guidelines Full Back Mode: 38-57 in, 40-100 lbs, 4+ years Backless Mode: 40-57 in, 40-100 lbs, 4+ years Included in the box: Oobr, Manual, Drink-thingy Accessories available for purchase separately Weelee travel bag, Cleaning Kit, and Mat-thingy. Clek Oobr High-Back and Backless Booster Seat with Rigid-LATCH installation, Adjustable Recline, 9-Year Expiration. The seat that grows with your child and is built like the seats in your car. Oobr is a high-back booster that revolutionizes booster seating. Its "firsts" include the rigid-LATCH system and a unique recline feature. When the time comes, it can be easily converted to backless. Want another reason to love Oobr? It’s been rated a 'Best Bet' by the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety for more than ten consecutive years! Free of Halogenated Flame Retardants, Because We're Parents Too. All Oobr models are free of brominated and chlorinated flame retardants, while the Mammoth and Railroad models are free of any added flame retardants. Oobr is proudly designed, engineered, and made in Canada.

Safety & Convenience Protective Sub-Structure Built with a high-impact copolymer frame, an energy-absorbing EPP foam reinforced headrest and a steel base sub-structure with integrated rigid-LATCH connectors for enhanced seat stability and safety performance. Installation Made Easy The Rigid-LATCH system locks Oobr into place, providing additional stability when your child is in the seat. When the seat is empty, the secure connection ensures that it won't become a projectile. Belt Guides Attached to the adjustable headrest, belt guides ensure proper belt fit on your child's hips and shoulders, each and every time. Reclining Seat Back Helps keep your child safe and comfortable when falling asleep in the car. Slide the seat forward using the Rigid-LATCH system and the free-pivoting seat back provides up to 12 degrees of recline for sleeping comfort (recline mode is NOT available if using the seat unanchored)

Engineered for Comfort as Your Child Grows The removable cushion allows for easy cleanups and provides an additional layer of comfort. Soft-touch armrests give added comfort. Oobr adapts to your growing child with its removable back feature converting it from a high back booster car seat to a backless booster. Ta-Dah! Protection Against Water-Based Stains Our C-Zero Plus Performance Collection is GREENGUARD Gold Certified and provides resistance to water-based stains using an innovative fluorine free formula. C-Zero Plus Performance fabrics are also free of halogenated flame retardants, and offer a moisture barrier to further improve cleanability and durability over the years. (Excludes Mammoth, tokidoki Rebel 2.0, Carbon and Railroad) Flame-Retardant Free Options Our Flame-Retardant free collection includes Mammoth, a blend of sustainably-sourced Merino wool + TENCEL, as well as Railroad. Both are OEKO-TEX Standard 100 certified and free of PFAS, PFOA, PFC and PFOS chemicals. Made in Canada Clek car seats are proudly manufactured in Ontario, Canada.

Clek is a Canadian based manufacturer of child passenger safety seats that combine safety with ease-of-use and modern style. Born out of a global automotive supplier, Clek offers the superior design, engineering best practices, world-class manufacturing, and craftsmanship found in luxury automotive seating today. We Make Car Seats for Parents Like Us Ride safe. Ride ride. Ride on. Safety: it’s the reason we’re doing this in the first place – to protect the wellbeing of our children and yours. From thoughtful design to impact-reducing materials, all of our baby and toddler car seats and booster car seats are equipped with innovative safety features. Our car seats aren’t just functional. They’re designed to make a statement, because you shouldn’t have to sacrifice style for safety. Made in Canada 9-year expiration for extended use Recyclable through Clek's Car Seat Recycling Program Free of Halogenated Flame Retardants Product Dimensions: 16 x 17 x 28 inches, 20 pounds Package Dimension: 28 x 17 x 13, 27 pounds

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute, Comfortable, and Clunky Free!
reviews.reviewText: I already have five carseats, but wanted something easier to secure my child. I found gold when I purchased this beauty. The design is sleek. Seat never appears crumby and repulsive. Easy seatbelt entrance and exit. Simple pull out under tray to lock back pieces into vehicle. One quick tilt to the side and tug to black strap to remove back from detachable seat. This seat costs what it does because it’s a creature of convenience and careful parent’s dream.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good booster. My daughter loves it.
reviews.reviewText: Clek never disappointed.My wife wanted to buy clek booster to match previous clek car seat foonf.Expensive than many other boosters out there. I have not tried the others but it is not that expensive considering my daughter is going to use this booster for next fee years.Sturdy and dutable as always.Easy to install.Backrest is removable as we need.Spill proof fabric for easy wipe off to clean.Armrest does not interfere while my kid put on/off seat belt.Light weight compare to foonf. ( foonf is heavy..)And my daughter feels comfortable and confidence.As mentioned, price is bit high compare to many others but if I break the price down with the length of time this seat will serve my kids, it is not too high for me to invest.Do I recommend this? Yes.Is it much better than the others? I don’t think so.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Durable and sleek
reviews.reviewText: We really liked our original convertible Clek carseat and wanted the next product to be from Clek. This booster seat didn't disappoint! It is comfortable and appears to be very well made. Our daughter likes it a lot! We got a cup holder too and it works well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super sturdy and heavy
reviews.reviewText: Super sturdy and heavy. This is a metal frame booster -- really solid! My only complaint is that the seat base is a little short, so if you kid has long legs, you need to recline it a little or the seat only comes to the middle of their thigh. Aside from that, its great. We bought two.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good safety ratings
reviews.reviewText: I chose this product for the safety ratings. The cup holder is flimsy. The armrests are with angles that I couldn't put on an activity tray.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 15, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Looks simple and sleep, but still feels very significant. Looking forward to buying a second one when our youngest is big enough for a booster.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this booster seat for it's safety
reviews.reviewText: Love this booster seat for it's safety, aesthetics, and functionality. The seat recline feature is nice on long car rides. It cleans fairly easily. It's heavier and bulkier than other boost seats, but I feel that it's very safe for my child. Worth the money!

reviews.reviewText: Es super suave y cómoda para la niña.
